+    "crash_safety": "rides the existing `apply_one` BEGIN IMMEDIATE wrapping SQL + PRAGMA user_version together; a failed step rolls back to 21 with BOTH columns absent (asserted by s22_failed_step_rolls_back_columns_and_version_together)",
+    "idempotence": "`migrate_with_event_sink` only applies steps with step_id > user_version — load-bearing because ALTER TABLE ADD COLUMN has no IF NOT EXISTS form (asserted by s22_is_idempotent_across_repeated_migrate_calls)",
+    "no_op_on_existing_data": "existing rows back-fill to NULL/NULL ⇒ unbounded ⇒ valid at every instant ⇒ default-view visibility unchanged (asserted against the raw table at seven instants including i64::MIN/MAX)",
+    "version_pins_updated": [
