+    "src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/slice10_read_view.rs": 12,
+    "src/rust/crates/fathomdb-engine/tests/slice10_node_validity.rs": 12
+  },
+  "mutation_verification": [
+    "Forced the BFS recursive-join node predicate to ignore the view (`ReadView::default()` instead of `view`): 3 RV tests FAILED, including `r_20_rv_graph_neighbors_view_applies_at_the_recursive_join` specifically. Restored and re-verified green.",
+    "Flipped the validity upper bound from `>` to `>=` (breaking the half-open convention): `r_20_nv_validity_window_matrix` FAILED. Restored and re-verified green.",
+    "Conclusion: neither suite is vacuously green."
+  ],
+  "uniform_application_evidence": {
+    "note": "The three per-direction BFS CTE copies (nine hand-written node predicates across anchor / recursive join / final projection) were folded into ONE template parameterised by the only two things that differ (edge join condition, traversed-to expression). Uniform application is therefore STRUCTURAL, not a thing to remember. Note the task brief said FOUR direction variants; there are in fact THREE `TraversalDirection` variants (Outgoing/Incoming/Both) — the fourth CTE is `build_bfs_with_depth_sql` for `search_expand`, which is NOT one of the five read verbs and was deliberately left on the strict path (unchanged behaviour).",
+    "positions_covered_by_separate_tests": ["anchor (all 3 directions)", "recursive join", "final projection"],
